<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-05-30T03:34:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-05-30T03:34:00-05:00" n="463" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d463">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/4397: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Harbin</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hanson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Harbin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-05-30T17:00:00+08:26"><hi rend="italic">May 30,
                                        1922—5 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 9:54
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>It appears that Wu Pei-fu’s adherents gaining control North Manchuria.
                            Local Chinese military insist that Japanese aiding mutineers. Reported
                            local Chinese merchants favor Wu.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hanson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>